i’m not sure what information i’m supposed to put, but i’m 14, female, 6’1 and in grief.


i knew that forgetfulness was normal right after my dad died, but lately it’s gotten even worse, and i cant even remember conversations i have with my friends, or if i was even with them that day. i usually have really good memory which is why i’m concerned. i also feel kind of like i’m in a dream, like i’m not really here.... and really exhausted. 

it’s been a month since my dad passed, and i’m only a teenager. i went to my doctor and she said she thinks it’s just stress because of his passing, but i went to the doctors a while ago and i wasn’t forgetting as important of things that i am now, like where i am or conversations i’m in. sometimes i have to turn to my friend and say “did i really just say that, or did i forget to say it out loud?”

does anyone have any advice or knows what this is? please help me out!

(edit: i’ve also been having a list of physical symptoms, but i’ve kind of ruled those out to being anxiety... paresthesia, aches and pains, headaches, etc)
